      <hedline>
        <hl1>Gay Pride, Anywhere</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Sarah Wright letter criticizes Vatican reaction to gay parade in Rome (July 9 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Gay Parade, Opposed by Vatican, Passes Peacefully in Rome'' (news article, July 9): One of the reasons that gays march anywhere is to show that we are people, too.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Gay Parade, Opposed by Vatican, Passes Peacefully in Rome'' (news article, July 9): One of the reasons that gays march anywhere is to show that we are people, too.</p>
        <p>Italy's Constitution may recognize that the family is founded in marriage, but it does not follow that nontraditional families are less deserving or that alternatives to marriage are immoral.</p>
        <p>The real provocation in Rome is the Vatican's attempt to override the primacy of conscience, a basic tenet of Catholic social justice teaching.</p>
        <p>SARAH WRIGHT  West Medford, Mass., July 9, 2000</p>
      </block>
